  "text": "It has not been possible to maintain many of the full length flavivirus infectious clones in bacteria. A cryptic bacterial promoter was identified in the 5′ NCR region of a full length DENV infectious clone [CITATION_1] . The N-terminally truncated polyprotein translated in bacteria from mRNA transcribed from this promoter was initiated at an inframe AUG located downstream of the one typically used for polyprotein translation.",
  "correct_citation": {
